        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1884907373" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12701481650440502955">I had never read a Tsukiyama book before, but was eager to, as I&apos;ve heard such good things about her work. She seems to be a little neglected, unfortunately and undeservedly. Whilst perusing Goodreads reviews, I plumped for <i>The Samurai&apos;s Garden</i> as my introduction to her work, as I loved the sound of the plot. <br/><br/>I was incredibly satisfied with this novel. There are so many themes which are addressed here - illness, family, society, secrecy, difference, loneliness - all of which were handled with th</span>
  <span id="freeText12701481650440502955" style="display:none">I had never read a Tsukiyama book before, but was eager to, as I've heard such good things about her work. She seems to be a little neglected, unfortunately and undeservedly. Whilst perusing Goodreads reviews, I plumped for <i>The Samurai's Garden</i> as my introduction to her work, as I loved the sound of the plot. <br /><br />I was incredibly satisfied with this novel. There are so many themes which are addressed here - illness, family, society, secrecy, difference, loneliness - all of which were handled with the utmost dexterity. <i>The Samurai's Garden</i> is a beautifully written, rather quiet, and contemplative novel, and I very much look forward to my next Tsukiyama on its strength.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12701481650440502955" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

