<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer16782038665689968918">Born to a Chinese mother and a Japanese father in San Francisco, Gail Tsukiyama now lives in El Cerrito, California. Her novels include <i>Women of the Silk</i> (1991), <i>The Samurai&apos;s Garden</i> (1995), <i>Night of Many Dreams</i> (1998), <i>The Language of Threads</i> (1999), <i>Dreaming Water</i> (2002), and <i>The Street of a Thousand Blossoms</i> (2007).</span>
  <span id="freeText16782038665689968918" style="display:none">Born to a Chinese mother and a Japanese father in San Francisco, Gail Tsukiyama now lives in El Cerrito, California. Her novels include <i>Women of the Silk</i> (1991), <i>The Samurai's Garden</i> (1995), <i>Night of Many Dreams</i> (1998), <i>The Language of Threads</i> (1999), <i>Dreaming Water</i> (2002), and <i>The Street of a Thousand Blossoms</i> (2007).</span>
  <a data-text-id="16782038665689968918" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

